First Lady Melania Trump and President Donald J. Trump will welcome President Emmanuel Macron and Mrs. Brigitte Macron of France for the Trump Administration's first state visit. The visit will include various activities, such as planting a European Sessile Oak tree on the South Lawn of the White House and a scenic tour of historic monuments in Washington. The state dinner will feature a cream and gold color scheme, with china settings from the Clinton and Bush administrations. The menu will showcase the best of America's cuisines and traditions, with French influences, and will be complemented by selected wines that embody the historic friendship between the United States and France. The guest list and First Lady's gown details will be released at the beginning of the dinner.